Operatives of the Ogun State Police Command have arrested two friends  for gang raping a 22-year-old girl at Eleweran Area of Abeokuta. The suspects, Seun Orokunle (38) and Sarumi Sodiq (28) were arrested following a complaint lodged at the Public Complaints Bureau Eleweran Abeokuta by the victim. The victim (name withheld) told the police  that the incident happened when she went to the house of  Seun Orokunle who happened to be her boyfriend. According to her, on getting there, she went to the bathroom to take bath and unknown to her Orokunle had invited his friend, Sarumi Sodiq, who came straight to meet her in the bathroom, dragged her out and the two of them took turns to have sex with her after beating her thoroughly. The victim said after satisfying themselves, Orokunle took her clothes and dipped it in a bucket of water in order to prevent her from leaving the house immediately. She stated further that the duo, who claimed to be cultists, threatened to kill her if she dared report them to anyone. The police spokesman in the state, Abimbola Oyeyemi, on Thursday, told newsmen that following the report, the officer in charge, Public Complaints Bureau, DSP Badmus Opeyemi, detailed his men to go after the two suspects. He said they were eventually traced to Aregbe area of Abeokuta where they were apprehended. Oyeyemi said both suspects had confessed to the crime. 